Class PulserTimer

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.rmit.agtgrp.apparate.gui.simviewer.model.timer.AEnvironTimer
      • au.edu.rmit.agtgrp.apparate.gui.simviewer.model.timer.PulserTimer

  • public class PulserTimer
extends AEnvironTimer
    This allows the environment to run for a certain amount of time before polling it for a result If no result available, it will re-poll again after a length of time
    Author:
    Andy Heng Xie

    • Constructor Detail

      • PulserTimer

        public PulserTimer(GridEnviron environ,
                   int pulseperiod,
                   int maxexecution,
                   int maxstepmillitime,
                   int maxmillitime)
        Parameters:
        environ - the environment to execute to
        pulseperiod - the polling period in millisecond, minimum is 40 millisecond
        maxexecution - the maximum number of polling, set -1 to be infinite
        maxstepmillitime - the maximum amount of time in millisecond to execute each step, set -1 to be infinite
        maxmillitime - the maximum amount of time in millisecond to execute, set -1 to be infinite
